case_circumstances: On September 07, 1993, the body of a unidentified white female was found by workers at a nearby aluminum transfer station; the workers spotted the body lying face down on the rocky bank of the Willamette River near Swan Island.  Some clothing was associated with the remains.  Several newspaper articles were written about the body and the request for information from anyone who may know her.  No information was ever developed.
